         <div type="commentary" subtype="general">
            <p>The Niceno-Constantinopolitan Creed from the Council of Chalcedon (451 CE) is copied here in this ostracon with some errors of spelling and some inserted text as follows: line 19 "for forgiving sins" (εἰς ἄφεσιν ἁμάρτιον) correct to "for the forgiveness of sins" (εἰς ἄφεσιν ἁμαρτιῶν) is added by mistake (a repeat of line 32 perhaps); line 36-37 are added an epilogue to the creed "one Lord, one faith, one baptism" and is verbatim quotation of Eph 4:5 (εἷς κύριος, μία πίστις, ἓν βάπτισμα); there are 3 christograms on the osctrac (line 1, 19, 36)</p>
         </div>
